[normal]Fitness to Practise[bold]2.
[normal]9
[normal]              
[normal]In 2012-13, we received
[normal] 
[normal]1
[normal],
[normal]657 
[normal]fitness to practise 
[normal]allegations
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]This amoun
[normal]ts to 0.53% of all registrants.
[normal] 248 cases were concluded at a final hearing
[normal] and 
[normal]panels 
[normal]imposed a 
[normal]striking-off order in 44 cases
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]2.1
[normal]0
[normal]              
[normal]We 
[normal]are always looking at ways to improve the efficiency of the fitness to practise process, whilst ensuring that the public continue to be protected. In
[normal] recent years this has included introducing the ability
[normal] for panels to agree the disposal
[normal] of suitable cases by consent
[normal] without the need for a contested hearing,
[normal] and the use of pre-hearing case management arrangements to ensure
[normal] the
[normal] timely
[normal] running of hearings
[normal]. In 2012-
[normal]13, the mean time taken from 
[normal]an allegation meeting our standard of acceptance
[normal] to consideration
[normal] by an Investigating Committee P
[normal]anel
[normal] (ICP)
[normal] was seven months. The mean time 
[normal]taken 
[normal]to conclusion at a final hearing was 16 months.
[normal]2.11
[normal]              
[normal]In its 2012-
[normal]13 performance review report, the PSA concluded that the HCPC was amongst those regulators 
[normal]‘
[normal]managing their caselo
[normal]ads effectively and efficiently’
[normal].
[normal]Education[bold]2.1
[normal]2
[normal]              
